The course provides an overview of various theories of creativity, and gives suggestions of  how to support a child's creativity. Students learn to find creative solutions through art.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of art education at pre-school and the field of technology at primary school as well as various creativity theories. To develop didactics competencies for teaching art at preschool.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student
1) will know the objectives, content and outcomes of art education at preschool; 
2) will know the aims and learning activities in the field of technology set for primary school in the National Curriculum;
3) will know different creativity theories and can foster a child's creativity;
4) can plan and carry out activities according to the curriculum and the age of children; 
5) will consider child development in teaching; 
6) can make samples using right techniques.
